## Domain model (aggregate, entities, value objects)

The full model is documented in [doc/domain-model.md](../../doc/domain-model.md). Summary:

- **Aggregate root**: **`SpeechAnalysisSession`** — one **`SpeechAnalyzer`**-backed session; single input-sequence semantics per Apple; explicit finalize/cancel lifecycle.
- **Entities**: **None required initially**; prefer value objects + session root until a stable concept needs identity (e.g. long-lived reserved locales).
- **Value objects**: **Extension types** for opaque handles (e.g. **`SpeechAnalysisSessionId`**); **immutable classes** for **transcriber configuration**, **asset status**, **transcription updates** / timing metadata streamed to callers.

